snippet.description:
From the makers of The Kashmir Files and The Tashkent Files, here is the official trailer of THE BENGAL FILES, the powerful conclusion to the trilogy by two-time National Award-winning filmmaker Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri.

A presentation by: Tej Narayan & Snehlatha Agarwal and I Am Buddha

Directed by: Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri
Produced by: Abhishek Agarwal, Pallavi Joshi and Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri 
Worldwide Release: Zee Studios
Music: Zee Music Co.
Starring: Mithun Chakraborty, Anupam Kher, Pallavi Joshi, Darshan Kumaar, Simratt Kaur

This September, witness the untold truth of the Hindu genocide.

It‚Äôs unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX ‚Äî interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything ‚Äî be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer ‚ÄúCapture the Flag‚Äù game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (‚ÄúRobux‚Äù). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

The S-class heroes gather and plan a raid on the Monster Association hideout to rescue the hostage. Meanwhile, Garou, a ‚Äúhuman monster‚Äù who was taken by the Monster Association during a battle with the heroes, awakens in the Monster Association hideout."

snippet.title: Bipul Chettri - Eh Saathi (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
'Eh Saathi' is the first release from the forthcoming album, 'Pravah'. As the title suggests, it's an ode to childhood friendships that transcends time. Almost written like a conversation piece put to music, the song embodies the notion of friendship that is something to nurture and celebrate, that you never take them for granted and its enduring nature of emphasizing loyalty, love, and the shared journey of life.

MUSIC
Bipul Chettri - Vocals, Guitars, Backing Vocals 
Pranai Gurung - Guitars
Rahul Rai - Bass
Rythem Bansal - Keys/Organ
Shantanu Sudarshan - Drums/Percussions 
Sumimardor Diengdoh, Bhushan Man Amatya, Prashansa Pandey Amatya - Backing Vocals 

Written and arranged by Bipul Chettri.
Recorded at Baa Baa Black Sheep Studios, Plug ‚ÄòN‚Äô Play Studios & Project Studio Productions.
Recording Engineers - Jonty Indra, Anindo Bose, Binaya Man Amatya 
Mixed & Mastered by Binaya Man Amatya
Album Cover Design - Manohar Rai
Album Cover Photography - Praveen Chettri
Producer - Bipul Chettri
Executive Producer - Sonam Tashi 

VIDEO
Directed by Dishant Pradhan
Director of Photography: Vashistha Pradhan 
Chief Assistant Director: Sujan Lamjel
Edited by: Dishant & Vazzu

Costume Designer: Pfulmaya

Production House: Lasta Studio 
Assistant Production Manager: Nuhang Subba 
Colorist: Shiny Syko
Lead Cast: Rahul N Mukhia, Kewal Subba, Tenzein Choden

en.title: Bipul Chettri - Eh Saathi (Official Music Video)
en.description:
'Eh Saathi' is the first release from the forthcoming album, 'Pravah'. As the title suggests, it's an ode to childhood friendships that transcends time. Almost written like a conversation piece put to music, the song embodies the notion of friendship that is something to nurture and celebrate, that you never take them for granted and its enduring nature of emphasizing loyalty, love, and the shared journey of life.

MUSIC
Bipul Chettri - Vocals, Guitars, Backing Vocals 
Pranai Gurung - Guitars
Rahul Rai - Bass
Rythem Bansal - Keys/Organ
Shantanu Sudarshan - Drums/Percussions 
Sumimardor Diengdoh, Bhushan Man Amatya, Prashansa Pandey Amatya - Backing Vocals 

Written and arranged by Bipul Chettri.
Recorded at Baa Baa Black Sheep Studios, Plug ‚ÄòN‚Äô Play Studios & Project Studio Productions.
Recording Engineers - Jonty Indra, Anindo Bose, Binaya Man Amatya 
Mixed & Mastered by Binaya Man Amatya
Album Cover Design - Manohar Rai
Album Cover Photography - Praveen Chettri
Producer - Bipul Chettri
Executive Producer - Sonam Tashi 

VIDEO
Directed by Dishant Pradhan
Director of Photography: Vashistha Pradhan 
Chief Assistant Director: Sujan Lamjel
Edited by: Dishant & Vazzu
Art Director: Tejistha Pradhan
Costume Designer: Pfulmaya
Assistant Costume Designer: Subeksha Gurung 
Assistant Cinematographer: Akash Pradhan 
Production House: Lasta Studio 
Assistant Production Manager: Nuhang Subba 
Colorist: Shiny Syko
Lead Cast: Rahul N Mukhia, Kewal Subba, Tenzein Choden

snippet.title: Mutu Mai Basecha - Female Version (Alternate/Extended) Bashiruddin Miyan
snippet.description:
Mutu Mae Basecha - Female Version (Alternate/Extended) Bashiruddin Miyan

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It‚Äôs unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX ‚Äî interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything ‚Äî be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer ‚ÄúCapture the Flag‚Äù game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (‚ÄúRobux‚Äù). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

‚ú® Achyutam Keshavam ‚Äì A Devotional Krishna Bhajan ‚ú®
 "Achyutam Keshavam" is a timeless and soul-soothing bhajan dedicated to Lord Krishna, praising their divine names, virtues, and forms. The bhajan beautifully recites various names of the Lord - Achyuta, Keshava, Narayana, and more - each carrying deep spiritual meaning.
Singing this bhajan is believed to purify the heart, remove sorrows, and bring the blessings of the Supreme Lord. It reminds devotees to surrender completely to God, trusting His eternal protection and grace.


üå∏ Chant ‚ÄúAchyutam Keshavam‚Äù with devotion and invite divine bliss into your life.
